## 🚀 How to Use

### Start Continuous Data Collection (2-minute intervals)
```powershell
.\continuous-simulator.ps1
```

**What it does:**
- Sends telemetry every **2 minutes**
- Shows timestamp and value for each reading
- Displays countdown: "Next reading in 2 minutes..."
- Press `Ctrl+C` to stop

**Example Output:**
```
[05:30:15] device-001 - temperature: 23.5°C ✓
[05:30:15] device-002 - humidity: 62.3% ✓
[05:30:15] device-003 - pressure: 1015.2hPa ✓

Next reading in 2 minutes...
```

### Send Historical Data (one-time)
```powershell
.\send-live-data.ps1
```

**What it does:**
- Generates 100 readings per device
- Each reading is 2 minutes apart
- Covers ~3.3 hours of historical data
- Timestamps go back in time from now

